x4freetext: - Detector
description
3.75 MV Van de Graaff accelerator
pulse width is 1 ns, repetition rate 250 kHz,
average beam current 1.5  microAmp
Metallic Li target of about 1 mg/cm2
.Proton beam energy adjusted so to be 30 and 100 keV
above the reaction 7-Li(p,n)7-Be threshold 1.881 MeV
giving neutrons in energy ranges 3-100, 3-200 keV
.Monitor sample Au-197, 0.3 mm == 2.2475E-4 atoms/b
thickness,weight 1.2990 gram, enclosing aluminium can
.Graphite sample 2.5 mm == 21.6874 atoms/b thickness,
0.7644 gram weight, enclosing aluminium can 0.2136 g
.Empty aluminium can 0.1810 gram
.Corrections were made on multiple scattering,
on neutron self-absorption, on undetected events
+ +  Compiled by S.Maev   + +

.Obtained by integrating cross-section from zero to
700 keV using different expressions for cross sect.,
namely - contribution I-1 at low energies 0 - 3 keV
is calculated in three different ways - first, from
statistical model calculations fitted to present
results and resonance parameters data. Second,
cross-sections from joint evaluated file was
normalized to present data from 3 to 10 keV. Third,
cross-sections were calculated according to Uhl`s
method. Contribution I-2 covers the range of present
experiment, for part I-3 above 225 keV this energy
range cross-sections were taken from joint evaluated
file.
